fields.name: Dessert
fields.description: A sweet course served at the end of a meal. Common desserts include cakes, ice creams, and pastries.

fields.name: Main Course
fields.description: The primary dish of a meal, typically more substantial and filling. Examples include steak, pasta, and roasted chicken.

fields.name: Salad
fields.description: A dish consisting of mixed vegetables, fruits, or grains, often served cold. Examples include Caesar salad, Greek salad, and fruit salad.

fields.name: Soup
fields.description: A liquid dish made by boiling ingredients such as meat, vegetables, or grains. Examples include tomato soup, chicken noodle soup, and minestrone.

fields.name: Side Dish
fields.description: A smaller dish served alongside the main course, often complementing its flavors. Examples include mashed potatoes, steamed vegetables, and rice

fields.name: Snack
fields.description: A small portion of food eaten between meals. Common snacks include chips, nuts, and fruit.

fields.name: Entree
fields.description: In some culinary traditions, this term refers to the main dish of a meal. In others, it can refer to a course served before the main course.

fields.name: Brunch
fields.description: A meal that combines breakfast and lunch, typically served in the late morning or early afternoon. Popular brunch items include eggs Benedict, pancakes, and mimosas.

fields.name: Buffet
fields.description: A style of meal service where guests serve themselves from a variety of dishes set out on a table or counter. Buffets often include a wide range of appetizers, main courses, and desserts.

fields.name: Vegetables
fields.description: Edible plants or parts of plants, typically consumed for their nutritional value, flavor, and texture. Examples include carrots, spinach, and bell peppers.

fields.name: Fruits
fields.description: Sweet or savory natural products of flowering plants, often consumed raw or used in desserts and salads. Examples include apples, bananas, and strawberries.

fields.name: Grains
fields.description: Seeds or fruits of cereal plants that are a staple food source, rich in carbohydrates and fiber. Examples include rice, wheat, and quinoa.

fields.name: Proteins
fields.description: Nutrient-rich foods that provide essential amino acids necessary for body functions. This category includes meat, fish, eggs, legumes, and nuts.

fields.name: Dairy
fields.description: Animal-derived products rich in calcium and protein, often used in cooking and baking. Examples include milk, cheese, and yogurt.

fields.name: Herbs and Spices
fields.description: Plants or parts of plants used to enhance flavor, aroma, and color in dishes. Examples include basil, cilantro, cinnamon, and black pepper.

fields.name: Oils and Fats
fields.description: Ingredients used for cooking and flavoring, providing richness and moisture to dishes. Examples include olive oil, butter, and coconut oil.

fields.name: Condiments
fields.description: Sauces and seasonings added to enhance the flavor of dishes. Examples include ketchup, mustard, soy sauce, and mayonnaise.

fields.name: Legumes
fields.description: Plants that produce seeds in pods, often high in protein and fiber. Common examples include beans, lentils, and chickpeas.

fields.name: Nuts and Seeds
fields.description: Edible seeds and fruits that are rich in healthy fats, protein, and nutrients. Examples include almonds, walnuts, sunflower seeds, and chia seeds.

fields.name: Carrot
fields.description: A root vegetable that is sweet and crunchy, rich in beta-carotene, fiber, and vitamins. Commonly used in salads, soups, and as snacks.

fields.name: Broccoli
fields.description: Green vegetable high in vitamins C and K; can be steamed or stir-fried.

fields.name: Spinach
fields.description: Leafy green packed with iron and vitamins; used in salads or cooked dishes.

fields.name: Bell Peppers
fields.description: Colorful, sweet vegetables high in vitamins A and C; versatile in many dishes.

fields.name: Zucchini
fields.description: Low-calorie summer squash; can be grilled, stuffed, or spiralized into noodles.

fields.name: Apples
fields.description: Crisp and sweet; high in fiber and vitamin C; great raw or in desserts.

fields.name: Bananas
fields.description: Soft, sweet fruit rich in potassium; commonly eaten raw or in smoothies.

fields.name: Strawberries
fields.description: Juicy berries high in antioxidants and vitamin C; excellent fresh or in sweets.

fields.name: Oranges
fields.description: Sweet, juicy citrus; high in vitamin C; often eaten fresh or juiced.

fields.name: Grapes
fields.description: Small, sweet fruits; can be eaten fresh, dried as raisins, or used for wine.

fields.name: Rice
fields.description: Staple food providing carbohydrates; used as a side dish or in many cuisines.

fields.name: Wheat
fields.description: Ground into flour; primary ingredient for bread, pasta, and baked goods.

fields.name: Oats
fields.description: Whole grain high in fiber; often used for breakfast in oatmeal or granola.

fields.name: Quinoa
fields.description: Gluten-free grain high in protein; versatile in salads and side dishes.

fields.name: Barley
fields.description: Hearty grain rich in fiber; commonly used in soups and stews.

fields.name: Chicken Breast
fields.description: Lean meat high in protein; versatile for grilling, baking, or stir-frying.

fields.name: Ground Beef
fields.description: Minced meat rich in protein; used in burgers, meatballs, and sauces.

fields.name: Salmon
fields.description: Fatty fish high in omega-3 fatty acids; often grilled or baked for flavor.

fields.name: Tofu
fields.description: Plant-based protein made from soy; absorbs flavors well; used in various dishes.

fields.name: Lentils
fields.description: Legumes high in protein and fiber; great in soups, salads, and veggie burgers.

fields.name: Whole Milk
fields.description: Rich in calcium and vitamins; used in cooking, baking, and as a drink.

fields.name: Cheddar Cheese
fields.description: Sharp and creamy cheese; popular in sandwiches, burgers, and snacks.

fields.name: Greek Yogurt
fields.description: Thick yogurt high in protein; eaten as a snack or used in dressings.

fields.name: Butter
fields.description: Creamy dairy fat; used for cooking, baking, and as a spread.

fields.name: Cream Cheese
fields.description: Soft cheese with a tangy flavor; commonly used in dips and desserts.

fields.name: Basil
fields.description: Fragrant herb used in Italian dishes; enhances sauces and salads.

fields.name: Cilantro
fields.description: Fresh herb with a citrusy flavor; popular in salsas and Asian dishes.

fields.name: Parsley
fields.description: Versatile herb used as a garnish; adds freshness to various dishes.

fields.name: Black Pepper
fields.description: Common spice for seasoning; adds heat and flavor to meals.

fields.name: Cinnamon
fields.description: Sweet and warm spice; used in baking and savory dishes for depth.

fields.name: Olive Oil
fields.description: Healthy fat rich in monounsaturated fats; used for cooking and dressings.

fields.name: Coconut Oil
fields.description: Solid at room temperature; used in baking and frying; adds a tropical flavor.

fields.name: Vegetable Oil
fields.description: Neutral oil used for frying and baking; versatile in many recipes.

fields.name: Sesame Oil
fields.description: Nutty oil often used in Asian cuisines; adds depth to stir-fries and dressings.

fields.name: Ketchup
fields.description: Sweet and tangy sauce; commonly used with fries and burgers.

fields.name: Mustard
fields.description: Tangy condiment; adds flavor to sandwiches and dressings.

fields.name: Soy Sauce
fields.description: Salty sauce used in Asian cooking; enhances the flavor of stir-fries.

fields.name: Mayonnaise
fields.description: Creamy condiment; used in sandwiches, salads, and dressings.

fields.name: Hot Sauce
fields.description: Spicy sauce; adds heat to dishes and can be used as a condiment.

fields.name: Chickpeas
fields.description: Versatile legumes used in hummus, salads, and stews.

fields.name: Black Beans
fields.description: Protein-rich beans often used in Mexican dishes and salads.

fields.name: Kidney Beans
fields.description: Heart-shaped beans great for chili and salads.

fields.name: Peas
fields.description: Sweet and tender; used in soups and as a side dish.

fields.name: Green Beans
fields.description: Crisp beans used in stir-fries and casseroles.

fields.name: Pinto Beans
fields.description: Creamy beans used in refried beans and chili.

fields.name: Split Peas
fields.description: Dried peas for soups; rich in protein and fiber.

fields.name: Almonds
fields.description: Crunchy nuts high in healthy fats; great as snacks or in baking.

fields.name: Walnuts
fields.description: Rich in omega-3s; used in baking and salads.

fields.name: Chia Seeds
fields.description: Tiny seeds packed with fiber; often added to smoothies.

fields.name: Flaxseeds
fields.description: Nutrient-rich seeds; commonly ground for cereals and smoothies.

fields.name: Sunflower Seeds
fields.description: Nutty seeds high in vitamin E; eaten raw or roasted.

fields.name: Salad
fields.description: Fresh and tasty dish!

fields.description: It's just a bakery
